2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6560aa3522cf74a5739c1eb8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20walking%20through%20a%20trench%20in%20October%202023%20near%20Bakhmut.%20Image%20used%20for%20illustration%20purposes%20only.%3Cp%3EKostya%20Liberov%2FLibkos%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20Bakhmut's%20northwestern%20edge%2C%20Russia%20had%20control%20over%20a%20vast%20maze%20of%20trenches.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUkrainian%20attempts%20to%20retake%20them%20had%20been%20a%20bloody%20failure.%20Then%20Special%20Forces%20were%20sent%20in.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOne%20soldier%20described%20the%20operation%20to%20Business%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EStepan%20Golian%20hadn't%20slept%20for%20two%20nights.%20He%20never%20did%2C%20ahead%20of%20a%20combat%20operation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20a%20small%20group%20of%20fellow%20Ukrainian%20Special%20Forces%20soldiers%2C%20he%20was%20readying%20himself%20to%20clear%20the%20pro-Kremlin%20mercenary%20Wagner%20Group%20from%20a%20network%20of%20trenches%20outside%20the%20bloody%20city%20of%20Bakhmut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20one%20of%20about%2045%20people%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbakhmut-how-ukraine-lost-city-russia-won-hollow-victory-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espoke%20to%20BI%20for%20a%20sweeping%20feature%20on%20the%20horrific%20fighting%20there%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20so%20many%20others%20defending%20Ukraine%2C%20Golian's%20military%20life%20began%20with%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20on%20February%2024%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20engineer%2C%20he%20signed%20up%20to%20fight%20that%20day%2C%20leaving%20behind%20a%20wife%20and%20a%20five-year-old%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGolian's%20group%20was%20often%20sent%20out%20on%20vanguard%20operations.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThat%20day%2C%20in%20mid-April%2C%20the%20task%20was%20on%20the%20northwestern%20outskirts%20of%20Bakhmut%2C%20a%20series%20of%20trenches%20protecting%20artillery%20positions%20from%20which%20Russia%20was%20bombarding%20a%20road%20the%20Ukrainians%20desperately%20needed%20to%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20O-0506%20road%20connects%20Bakhmut%20to%20the%20village%20of%20Khromove%20and%20then%20to%20Chasiv%20Yar%2C%20from%20where%20Ukraine's%20forces%20were%20supplying%20those%20on%20the%20city's%20front%20line%20and%20treating%20its%20wounded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWinning%20the%20road%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20only%20two%20still-usable%20routes%20%E2%80%94%20would%20tighten%20Wagner's%20grip%20on%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20vehicle%20on%20the%20road%20to%20Bakhmut%20via%20Khromove%2C%20amid%20dust%20and%20smoke%2C%20on%20March%204%2C%202023%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6560a76d22cf74a5739c1d87%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20vehicle%20on%20the%20road%20to%20Bakhmut%20via%20Khromove%20in%20March%202023.%3Cp%3EEvgeniy%20Maloletka%2FAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20time%20the%20losses%20in%20that%20area%20of%20the%20front%20were%20very%2C%20very%20high%20for%20both%20sides%2C%26quot%3B%20Golian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20estimated%20that%20for%20every%20Ukrainian%20killed%2C%20Russia%20was%20losing%20seven%20Wagner%20fighters%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20were%20constantly%20receiving%20waves%20of%20fresh%20troops%20to%20capture%20the%20trenches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20artillery%20advantage%20was%20also%20huge%2C%C2%A0and%20it%20was%20responsible%20for%20about%2090%25%20of%20Ukrainian%20deaths%2C%20he%20estimated.%20Ukraine%20only%20had%20a%20quarter%20of%20that%20firepower%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20units%20had%20gone%20on%20ahead%20of%20Golian's%20group%2C%20and%20the%20news%20over%20the%20radio%20was%20bad%20%E2%80%94%20there%20were%20major%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20his%20group%20set%20out%20for%20the%20trenches%20in%20their%20BMPs%2C%20a%20Soviet-era%20infantry%20fighting%20vehicle.%20One%20of%20them%20was%20struck%20by%20an%20anti-tank%20missile%20on%20the%20way.%20Those%20who%20survived%20pushed%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20had%20been%20fighting%20here%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time.%20The%20area%20was%20%26quot%3Babsolutely%20covered%26quot%3B%20with%20the%20dead%2C%20he%20said%2C%2040%20to%2050%20bodies%20that%20nobody%20could%20collect%20because%20the%20area%20was%20too%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20stretching%20ahead%2C%20across%20several%20miles%2C%20was%20a%20labyrinth%20of%20trenches%20to%20be%20retaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%20three%20and%20six%20feet%20deep%2C%20some%20of%20the%20trenches%20were%20flooded%2C%20with%20the%20water%20up%20to%20his%20waist.%20Others%20had%20been%20wrecked%20by%20artillery%20fire.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGolian%20said%20their%20way%20of%20moving%20ahead%20was%20twofold.%20You%20advance%2C%20using%20your%20machine%20gun%20or%20submachine%20gun%20to%20fire%20ahead%20of%20you%2C%20and%2C%20if%20you%20encounter%20an%20obstacle%2C%20you%20throw%20a%20grenade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20soldiers%20were%20supposed%20to%20have%20at%20least%2020%20grenades%20each.%20Covering%20each%20other%20with%20fire%2C%20they%20would%20%26quot%3Bcleanse%26quot%3B%20the%20area%20and%20move%20forward%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20would%20gather%20extra%20ammunition%20as%20they%20went%2C%20exactly%20as%20any%20videogamer%20might%20imagine%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20every%20point%20of%20active%20connection%20with%20the%20enemy%2C%20there%20are%20lots%20of%20weapons%20and%20ammunition%20just%20lying%20around%2C%26quot%3B%20Golian%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20submachine%20guns%2C%20machine%20guns%2C%20anti-tank%20grenades%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BYou%20just%20pick%20it%20up%20and%20keep%20fighting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThreats%20also%20came%20from%20above.%20%26quot%3BAt%20any%20point%20in%20time%20there%20are%20six%2C%20seven%2C%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20%E2%80%94%20drones%20%E2%80%94%20sitting%20in%20the%20sky%20above%20your%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAll%20of%20those%20drones%20were%20completing%20reconnaissance%20work%26quot%3B%20to%20guide%20artillery%20fire%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20most%20were%20Russian%2C%20in%20his%20estimation.%20It%20meant%20there%20could%20be%20no%20pausing%20%E2%80%94%20stay%20still%20for%20more%20than%20a%20couple%20of%20minutes%20and%20you'd%20risk%20an%20artillery%20strike%20on%20your%20head.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20now%2C%20any%20overnight%20anxiety%20was%20long%20gone.%20It%20was%20time%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20no%20feelings%20about%20this.%20There%20are%20no%20feelings%2C%26quot%3B%20Golian%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20the%20emotions%2C%20they're%20switched%20off.%20You%20live%20on%20the%20skills%20that%20you%20acquired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGolian%20finds%20it%20hard%20to%20explain%20how%20he%20deals%20with%20the%20fear.%20On%20the%20morning%20of%20an%20operation%20like%20this%20%26quot%3Bsomething%20like%20a%20psychological%20protection%26quot%3B%20switches%20on%20in%20his%20head%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20the%20long%20bloody%20day%2C%20he%20and%20his%20small%20group%20recaptured%20several%20hundred%20feet%20of%20trenches%2C%20ready%20for%20other%20Ukrainian%20troops%20to%20move%20into%20and%20hold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20lost%20comrades.%20He%20was%20also%20struck%20by%20a%20120mm%20shell%20that%20wounded%20his%20leg.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20he%20considers%20himself%20lucky.%20%26quot%3BI've%20seen%20enough%20pictures%20when%20boys%2C%20guys%20were%20losing%20all%20of%20their%20limbs.%20They%20were%20losing%20a%20whole%20leg%2C%20whole%20arm%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20see%20those%20pictures%20ar