2%80%9CWe%E2%80%99ll%20put%20a%20shawl%20and%20a%20lipstick%20on%20him.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20worst%20fear%20had%20just%20been%20confirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERehearsals%20were%20held%20for%20the%20play%20every%20morning%20and%20every%20evening%20for%202%20weeks.%20Also%20part%20of%20the%20play%20were%20Christmas%20carols%20to%20be%20performed%20by%20a%20choir%20of%2012%20Nigerian%20inmates.%20They%20looked%20good%20on%20stage%20and%20moved%20well%20together%20as%20they%20sang.%20The%20only%20problem%20was%20that%20most%20of%20them%20were%20tone%20deaf%20and%20Chuck%20and%20Thomas%2C%20the%20biggest%20and%20worst%20tempered%20of%20the%20lot%2C%20did%20not%20get%20along.%20But%20these%20were%20minor%20issues%20in%20the%20larger%20scheme%20of%20things.%20We%20had%20bigger%20things%20to%20worry%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20toughest%20part%20of%20the%20production%2C%20however%2C%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20the%20choir!%20They%20just%20could%20not%20carry%20a%20tune.%20With%20only%20ten%20days%20to%20go%20for%20the%20first%20show%20and%20tensions%20running%20high%2C%20I%20called%20a%20friend%20who%20owned%20a%20studio%20and%20asked%20him%20for%20advice.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CLet%20me%20create%20music%20tracks%20for%20you%20that%20these%20chaps%20can%20sing%20on.%20Make%20sure%20the%20music%20is%20louder%20than%20the%20vocals.%20It%20just%20might%20work.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20it%20did!%20The%20singers%20were%20thrilled%20to%20discover%20that%20they%20actually%20could%20sing%20karaoke%20style%20to%20backing%20music%20tracks.%20So%20inspired%20were%20they%20with%20their%20new%20ability%20to%20sound%20melodic%20that%20they%20practiced%20for%20two%20days%20straight%20without%20fighting%20and%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20the%20second%20day%20managed%20to%20sing%20%3Cem%3EJingle%20Bells%2C%20O%20Come%20All%20Ye%20faithful%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ESilent%20Night%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20the%20same%20key.%20The%20relief%20was%20huge.%20They%20fist%20bumped%20and%20high-fived%2C%20and%20that%20night%20I%20slept%20in%20peace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDecember%2018%2C%201994.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20day%20of%20the%20first%20Christmas%20show%20arrived.%20The%20Tihar%20Theatre%20Troupe%20was%20to%20debut%20in%20Jail%20No.%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENigel%2C%20every%20inch%20the%20nervous%20director%2C%20gave%20last%20minute%20instructions%20to%20the%20actors%20who%20took%20up%20positions%20behind%20the%20stage.%20The%202000-strong%20population%20of%20the%20jail%20filed%20into%20the%20%3Cem%3Echakkar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20common%20area%20used%20for%20cultural%20events%20and%20started%20sitting%20in%20rows%20under%20the%20watchful%20eyes%20of%20the%20white%20%3Cem%3Ekurta%20pajama%3C%2Fem%3E%20clad%20%3Cem%3Enumberdaars%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20convicts%20charged%20with%20maintaining%20order%20amongst%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20inmates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20327px)%2085vw%2C%20327px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F25121447%2F81LnlRllM5L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22327%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F25121447%2F81LnlRllM5L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_.jpg%20625w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F25121447%2F81LnlRllM5L._AC_UF10001000_QL80_-188x300.jpg%20188w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-690663%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22523%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERohit%20Kumar%3Cbr%3E%3Cem%3ETales%20from%20the%20Jail%20%E2%80%93%20Christmas%20in%20Tihar%20and%20Other%20Stories%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3ENotion%20Press%2C%202016%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20something%20unnerving%20about%20looking%20out%20over%20a%20sea%20of%20prison%20inmates%20sitting%20cross-legged%20in%20neat%20rows%20and%20waiting%20for%20a%20show%20to%20begin.%20Events%20at%20Tihar%20were%20carried%20out%20in%20style.%20Marigold%20garlands%20festooned%20the%20gigantic%20concrete%20stage%2C%20carpets%20covered%20it%20and%20a%20podium%20waited%20off%20to%20the%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20was%20in%20English%20and%20since%20it%20needed%20a%20running%20translation%20in%20Hindi%2C%20I%20had%20volunteered%20to%20be%20the%20narrator-translator.%20There%20are%20things%20I%20have%20done%20years%20ago%20which%20still%20bring%20a%20smile%20to%20my%20face.%20Helping%20Nigel%20organize%20his%20play%20is%20one%20of%20them.%20Being%20his%20running%20translator%20is%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20began.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20I%20had%20believed%20till%20that%20point%20that%20two%20thousand%20prisoners%20were%20going%20to%20watch%20a%20Christmas%20play%20performed%20by%20foreign%20inmates%20in%20respectful%20and%20appreciative%20silence%20I%20still%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20But%20the%20moment%20%E2%80%98Mary%E2%80%99%20walked%20on%20to%20the%20stage%2C%20I%20realized%20respect%20and%20silence%20were%20not%20going%20to%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%2C%20if%20you%20recall%2C%20was%20a%20tall%2C%20bald%20Dutchman.%20Dressed%20in%20a%20red%20saree%2C%20head%20covered%20by%20a%20brown%20shawl%2C%20and%20sporting%20a%20bright%20red%20bindi%20and%20even%20brighter%20lipstick%2C%20he%20looked%20grotesque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CJe%20kaun%20hai%20be%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%E2%80%9CWho%20the%20heck%20is%20that%3F%E2%80%9D)%20asked%20an%20inmate%20sitting%20in%20the%20front%20row%20in%20coarse%20Haryanvi%20in%20a%20stage%20whisper%20loud%20enough%20to%20be%20heard%20by%20at%20least%20thirty%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CManne%20toh%20vilayeti%20kinnar%20lage!%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(%E2%80%9CLooks%20like%20a%20foreign%20eunuch%20to%20me.%E2%80%9D)%20responded%20his%20friend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20not%20going%20as%20expected.%20And%20it%20was%20just%20the%20beginning.%20Jail%20No.%204%20was%20about%20to%20witness%20the%20most%20unintentionally%20funny%20comedy%20they%20had%20ever%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENigel%20narrated%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20town%20of%20Nazareth%20lived%20a%20young%20woman%20called%20Mary.%20Mary%20had%20found%20favour%20with%20God.%20One%20night%20as%20she%20was%20sleeping%2C%20an%20angel%20entered%20the%20room.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20translated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20angel%20%E2%80%98Gabriel%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20jovial%20Italian%20walked%20onto%20stage%20with%20a%20decidedly%20un-angelic%20swagger.%20He%20stood%20over%20Mary%2C%20stretched%20out%20his%20arms%2C%20and%20announced%20in%20a%20singsong%20voice%2C%20%E2%80%9CHail%20Mary%2C%20full%20of%20grace%2C%20the%20Lord%20is%20with%20you!%20You%20are%20going%20to%20blessed%20with%20a%20son%20who%20will%20be%20known%20as%20the%20Saviour%20of%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%2C%20expressing%20appropriate%20awe%2C%20replied%20in%20thick%20Dutch%20accented%20English%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20how%20can%20this%20be%2C%20seeing%20I%20have%20never%20known%20a%20man%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20did%20not%20bother%20to%20translate%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20play%20progressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20(in%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CHey%2C%20Mary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%20(in%20equally%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CYes%2C%20Joseph%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20(in%20deep%20voice)%3A%20%E2%80%9CBethlehem%20is%20crowded.%20All%20the%20inns%20are%20full.%20What%20are%20we%20going%20to%20do%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMary%3A%20(in%20equally%20deep%20voice)%20%E2%80%9CPlease%2C%20we%20have%20to%20find%20a%20room.%20I%20am%20going%20to%20give%20birth.%20The%20baby%20is%20about%20to%20come.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20audience%20dissolved%20in%20peals%20of%20laughter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20Baby%20Jesus%20(a%20cloth%20doll)%20was%20about%20to%20come%20into%20the%20world%2C%20Joseph%20knelt%20beside%20Mary%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CCome%20on%2C%20Mary%2C%20push!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%20I%20heard%20someone%20in%20the%20audience%20mimicking%20a%20baby%E2%80%99s%20cry.%20Others%20imitated%20and%20soon%20about%20a%20thousand%20people%20joined%20suit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%20it%20happened!%20The%20moment%20of%20Jesus%E2%80%99%20birth!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoseph%20stood%20up%2C%20holding%20not%20a%20cloth%20doll%20but%20a%20real%20live%20baby%20in%20his%20arms!%20The%20crowd%20went%20wild.%20I%20lost%20my%20power%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20later%20discovered%2C%20some%20of%20our%20actors%20%E2%80%93%20the%20shepherds%20to%20be%20precise%20%E2%80%93%20had%20discovered%20a%20baby%20behind%20the%20stage.%20It%20was%20the%20child%20of%20a%20woman%20labourer%20who%20along%20with%20others%20had%20been%20brought%20into%20the%20jail%20to%20do%20construction%20work.%20The%20actors%20had%20%E2%80%98borrowed%E2%80%99%20the%20baby%20and%20managed%20to%20pass%20it%20on%20to%20Mary%20and%20Joseph%20on%20stage.%20It%20was%20a%20defining%20moment%20in%20the%20drama.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20kings%20%E2%80%93%20dressed%20in%20Indian%20king%20costumes%20replete%20with%20Indian%20crowns%20and%20Indian%20beads%20%E2%80%93%20walked%20in%20and%20offered%20%E2%80%98gifts%20of%20gold%2C%20frankincense%20and%20myrrh%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%20And%20as%20they%20knelt%20before%20Indian%20baby%20Jesus%2C%20the%20choir%20walked%20up%20on%20stage%2C%20surrounded%20the%20nativity%20scene%20and%20sang%20%E2%80%98Silent%20Night%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20will%20never%20forget%20the%20silence%20that%20followed.%20The%20Nigerian%20choir%20sang%20pitch-perfect.%20They%20were%20magical!%20Was%20this%20the%20same%20choir%20that%20had%20come%20to%20blows%20just%20days%20before%3F%20The%20actors%20joined%20in%20as%20did%20those%20few%20in%20the%20audience%20who%20knew%20the%20carol.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CSilen