ways%20is%20expected%20to%20slow%20down%20in%20FY25%20on%20account%20of%20decline%20in%20projects%20awarded%20during%20FY24.%20Projects%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20just%202%2C817%20km%20were%20awarded%20till%20November%202023%2C%20compared%20to%205%2C382%20km%20during%20the%20same%20period%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20Road%20Transport%20and%20Highways%20(MoRTH)%20said%20that%20approvals%20need%20to%20be%20expedited%20for%20the%20revised%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20project%20or%20any%20alternative%20programme%20to%20meet%20the%20targeted%20awards%20for%20FY24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shortfall%20may%20worsen%20with%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20effect%20during%20January-March%202024.%20March%20typically%20sees%20a%20significant%20percentage%20of%20road%20project%20awards%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EICRA%2C%20a%20ratings%20agency%2C%20predicted%20a%20lower%20overall%20award%20in%20FY24%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20year%2C%20cutting%20its%20forecast%20to%207%2C000-7%2C500%20km%2C%20a%2040-43%25%20decline%20year-on-year.%20The%20delay%20in%20Cabinet%20approval%20for%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20has%20also%20slowed%20the%20project%20awarding%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBreaking%20down%20the%20awarding%20process%2C%20Modani%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Flogistics%2Fa-slow-stretch-lies-ahead%2Farticle67669673.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20%3Cem%3Ebusinessline%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20award%2C%20say%2C%20in%20July%2C%20August%20or%20September%2C%20then%20financial%20closure%20and%20so%20on%20happen%20six%20months%20down%20the%20line%2C%20ahead%20of%20the%20appointed%20date.%20So%2C%20it%20generally%20takes%208-9%20months%20for%20work%20to%20begin%20after%20the%20awarding.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccordingly%2C%20FY24%20will%20not%20be%20impacted%20because%20most%20projects%20are%20underway%20at%20a%20comfortable%20clip.%20However%2C%20if%20there%20is%20a%20slowdown%20in%20awarding%20during%20the%20current%20fiscal%2C%20then%20execution%20will%20be%20impacted%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%20FY25%20and%2C%20subsequently%2C%20FY26%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ICRA%2C%20there%20is%20a%20preference%20for%20the%20%E2%80%98engineering%2C%20procurement%2C%20and%20construction%E2%80%99%20(EPC)%20route%20in%20road%20project%20awards%2C%20with%20a%20gradual%20shift%20towards%20%E2%80%98build%2C%20operate%20and%20transfer%E2%80%99%20(BOT)-toll%20projects%20which%20require%20less%20funding%20support%20from%20the%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBharatmala%20Phase-I%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20has%20also%20decided%20to%20extend%20the%20completion%20deadline%20for%20the%20flagship%20highway%20development%20project%2C%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%2C%20from%202022%20to%202027-28.%20The%20six-year%20delay%20from%20the%20original%20schedule%20is%20primarily%20driven%20by%20a%20more%20than%20100%25%20increase%20in%20the%20estimated%20cost%20of%20the%20project%20which%20is%20now%20standing%20at%20nearly%20Rs%2011%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20ministry%20of%20road%20transport%20and%20highways%E2%80%99%20endeavour%20to%20award%20all%20projects%20on%20completion%20of%20land%20acquisition%20and%20obtaining%20all%20clearances%20by%20the%20end%20of%202024-25%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20told%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20length%20of%2034%2C800%20km%2C%20approximately%2076%25%2C%20or%2026%2C418%20km%2C%20of%20highway%20stretches%20have%20been%20awarded%20so%20far.%20Despite%20this%20progress%2C%20the%20first%20eight%20months%20of%20the%20current%20financial%20year%20have%20seen%20only%20102%20km%20of%20projects%20under%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20being%20awarded%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pace%20of%20awarding%20projects%20is%20expected%20to%20further%20slow%20down%20until%20the%20Cabinet%20Committee%20on%20Economic%20Affairs%20(CCEA)%20sanctions%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20the%20project.%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Finance%20has%20imposed%20restrictions%2C%20barring%20the%20highways%20ministry%20from%20creating%20any%20fresh%20liability%20under%20the%20project%20until%20CCEA%20approval%20is%20secured.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20extended%20completion%20deadline%20set%20for%202027-28%2C%20only%2042%25%2C%20or%2015%2C045%20km%2C%20of%20the%20project%20had%20been%20completed%20as%20of%20November-end%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3EFinancial%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20committee%20initially%20approved%20the%20first%20phase%20in%202017%2C%20estimating%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%205.35%20trillion.%20However%2C%20the%20sanctioned%20cost%20of%20awarded%20projects%20has%20surpassed%20Rs%208.5%20trillion%2C%20prompting%20the%20Public%20Investment%20Board%20to%20appraise%20the%20revised%20cost%20of%20Bharatmala%20Phase-I%20at%20Rs%2010.95%20trillion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703491345000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F26130435%2F30501593928_465a2ee4cf_c-e1682494521102.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flull-in-highway-construction-expected-in-fy25-flagship-highway-projected-faces-6-year-delay%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20shortfall%20may%20worsen%20with%20the%20model%20code%20of%20conduct%20for%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20in%20e